#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:120
msgid "Serves <code>/.well-known/api-catalog</code> as <code>application/linkset+json</code> per RFC 9727."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:121
msgid "Each linkset entry advertises service-desc (the OpenAPI spec, when that toggle is on), service-doc (WordPress REST API handbook), and status (the plugin's public health endpoint)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:122
msgid "Also emits <code>Link: &lt;url&gt;; rel=\"api-catalog\"</code> on every frontend response so agents discover the catalog from any URL."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:125
msgid "Serves <code>/.well-known/mcp/server-card.json</code> per the SEP-1649 draft so MCP-aware agents can discover the site."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:126
msgid "serverInfo (name, version, description, websiteUrl) is generated from get_bloginfo() so it stays accurate per subsite."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:127
msgid "Declares a transport endpoint, capability objects, protocolVersion, and instructions pointing agents at the API catalog and OpenAPI spec."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:130
msgid "Serves <code>/.well-known/agent-skills/index.json</code> listing six skills (content-query, posts-read, pages-read, media-library, categories, tags) per the Agent Skills Discovery RFC v0.2.0."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:131
msgid "Each skill also ships a deterministic SKILL.md artifact at <code>/.well-known/agent-skills/{name}/SKILL.md</code>."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:132
msgid "Index entries carry a sha256 digest of the served SKILL.md bytes so agents can verify artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:135
msgid "Serves <code>/auth.md</code> documenting how agents authenticate via Application Passwords: creation by a human account owner, Basic-auth usage, scope, and revocation."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:136
msgid "Honest by design: it notes when Application Passwords are unavailable and never advertises OAuth endpoints the site doesn't have."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:139
msgid "Serves <code>/llms.txt</code> — a curated Markdown index (site identity, top-level pages, recent posts with cleaned excerpts) per llmstxt.org, with a Discovery section auto-linking every other enabled plugin endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:140
msgid "<code>/llms-full.txt</code> serves the full content of recent posts and pages converted to Markdown. Password-protected content is always excluded from both."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:141
msgid "Cached for one hour; invalidates automatically on post changes, site identity changes, and toggle changes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:144
msgid "On publish, fires a single non-blocking POST to <code>api.indexnow.org</code> with exactly <code>{ host, key, urlList }</code> — Bing and Yandex re-crawl within minutes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:145
msgid "Skips revisions, autosaves, and non-public post types; serves the key file at <code>/{key}.txt</code> for ownership verification."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:148
msgid "Watches for <code>Accept: text/markdown</code>; browsers asking for HTML get the normal response, and <code>Vary: Accept</code> keeps caches from mixing the variants."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:149
msgid "Buffers the rendered HTML, extracts the main content region, and converts it to clean Markdown."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:150
msgid "Returns <code>Content-Type: text/markdown</code> and <code>X-Markdown-Tokens</code> (≈ chars/4) so agents can budget context size."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:153
msgid "Outputs a <code>&lt;script type=\"application/ld+json\"&gt;</code> block in the head."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:154
msgid "Always includes WebSite (with SearchAction) and Organization (logo resolved from your theme's custom logo or site icon); singular posts add Article and BreadcrumbList; FAQ-shaped content adds FAQPage."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:155
msgid "Auto-suppresses when an SEO plugin (Yoast, Rank Math, AIOSEO, etc.) is active to prevent duplicate structured data."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:158
msgid "Serves <code>/openapi.json</code> (and legacy <code>?format=openapi</code>) — a complete OpenAPI 3.0.3 document."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:159
msgid "Built from every registered REST route (honoring show_in_index), so plugin routes appear automatically; WordPress regex placeholders become templated paths with proper path/query/requestBody parameters."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:160
msgid "Cached for one day; invalidates on plugin activation/deactivation and theme switch."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:163
msgid "A frontend script registers four read-only tools (search_content, get_posts, get_pages, get_site_info) on <code>navigator.modelContext</code> — the W3C WebMCP draft API."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:164
msgid "Subsite-aware, and a silent no-op in browsers without the experimental API."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:167
msgid "Adds one robots.txt group per AI crawler from the policy table: allowed bots get WordPress core's wp-admin rules replicated; blocked bots get <code>Disallow: /</code>."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:168
msgid "Honors \"Discourage search engines\" — while that Reading setting is on, every managed bot is blocked regardless of policy."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:171
msgid "Appends a <code>Content-Signal</code> directive built from your yes/no preferences, inside an explicit <code>User-agent: *</code> group at the end of robots.txt."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/help-tabs.php:172
msgid "Composes with SEO plugins — their robots.txt additions are preserved; our directive lands last."
msgstr ""

